    <node id="&quot;WEIBO&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">Weibo is a prominent social media platform in China that serves as a space for users to share updates, express views, and interact with one another. It plays a significant role in the dissemination of information, particularly during critical events such as the coronavirus outbreak, where users discuss topics like the shortage of face masks and share their experiences related to the health crisis. The platform allows users to post content, including diary entries, and engage with friends and followers, reflecting an informal communication style.

However, Weibo has faced criticism for its censorship practices, including account shutdowns and the deletion of posts that violate its guidelines. Users have reported experiences of online attacks and negative comments, highlighting the platform's dual nature as a space for both expression and public judgment. The author of the descriptions has utilized Weibo to document their thoughts and experiences, including responding to accusations regarding their actions during a personal crisis, but has also encountered challenges such as having their account frozen and posts deleted.

Overall, Weibo is a multifaceted social media platform that facilitates communication and information sharing while also grappling with issues of censorship and user safety.</data>
      <data key="d2">2c5e9cdd8d1ed971c72785d384814175,3b5ca06477ea6649725a16d09d87927a,8119bda66f27343b4be177610dcff2af,8124652946d2a60444c90e0a3706521b,8475b5acce1676914c613935d50901d6,9588379e66312b7114543c3aed2a9b4b,9d1b23dde4b17acb2dfd0472a9ab0471,a258c0fe44c182e59b2af3913158bbf1,a47098bdb1e8c07bb54ff29a75698044,c45145c12a7fedd7064529e344fa3e04,c7d14067bee9b74c3ed5d2f5b7f20d6e,db3e66e7b4d19ca23e8d685bcc43901c,ecdbc80cd38edf6145de3f6de4c35bb9,ee747c2b3ef4b0d990341dab895eb81d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;SINA&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Sina is the company that operates Weibo, known for its lack of responsiveness to user complaints."</data>
      <data key="d2">2c5e9cdd8d1ed971c72785d384814175</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CHENG YONGXIN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Cheng Yongxin is an editor for the literary journal Harvest who suggested the idea of writing a series called 'Wuhan Diary' to document experiences during the quarantine."</data>
      <data key="d2">2c5e9cdd8d1ed971c72785d384814175</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WUHAN DIARY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Wuhan Diary" is a personal account that offers valuable insights into the outbreak of COVID-19 in Wuhan. It is recommended by a doctor for those seeking the truth about the situation in the city. Additionally, "Wuhan Diary" is envisioned as a series of writings aimed at sharing the experiences and realities of life during the quarantine in Wuhan, capturing the challenges and circumstances faced by individuals during this unprecedented time.</data>
      <data key="d2">2c5e9cdd8d1ed971c72785d384814175,4c986d95fbf69302998d67747722f245</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;LUNAR NEW YEAR&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">Lunar New Year is a significant cultural celebration that marks the beginning of the new year in the lunar calendar, widely observed in many Asian countries, particularly in China. This year, the celebration is particularly notable as it is occurring during a time of public health crisis, specifically the outbreak of the coronavirus. The event, which is traditionally a time for family gatherings and festivities, has been heavily impacted by the ongoing quarantine measures, leading to canceled gatherings and altered traditions. 

As the celebration unfolds, it is marked as Day Nine, highlighting the ongoing nature of the festivities. However, the atmosphere is overshadowed by the urgency of the situation, as individuals, including the narrator, find themselves attempting to buy face masks amidst the health crisis. The outbreak has also affected travel dynamics, with many people leaving Wuhan, which has significantly altered the city's population during this critical time.

Additionally, the Singapore government has arranged evacuation flights for residents, including the narrator's niece, further illustrating the disruption caused by the outbreak. The overall sentiment during this year's Lunar New Year is one of grief and loss, as the traditional celebrations are overshadowed by the health crisis, impacting the public's response and the cultural significance of the holiday.</data>
      <data key="d2">05facbc17efc22acf453283e5f155f6b,0bc629e093e4342af5865fab7f58e2ed,2c5e9cdd8d1ed971c72785d384814175,3f8704dd72f25d452df3dea8b46c7b79,4ff73e560b2adc17ec7edf9507bb1ecf,679f442d0cee20509148a0adeb4ebc0a,941fd97efac4d3db43e927529ff925c4,96d1b9c58350b57745013c6971a006ff,a47098bdb1e8c07bb54ff29a75698044,c74fab649e0e555219cd986800fcd418,e8105e46cc3831c70abcbabad8edbcaf,ee747c2b3ef4b0d990341dab895eb81d</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;HUBEI&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">Hubei is a province in China, with Wuhan as its capital, that has been at the center of a significant health crisis due to a coronavirus outbreak. This province has faced critical health challenges, becoming the epicenter of the outbreak, which has severely impacted its residents and economy. The outbreak has led to employment crises for migrant workers and has necessitated medical volunteer efforts and community responses to address the urgent needs of the population.

During the crisis, Hubei has been under quarantine, affecting daily life and economic activities for its residents. The province has also experienced exclusionary policies from Beijing, which have further complicated the situation for its inhabitants. Reports indicate that there have been vegetable donations and other forms of aid to support those affected by the outbreak.

Despite the severe challenges, Hubei is showing signs of improvement, with fluctuating infection rates and ongoing government responses to manage the outbreak. The province has been a focal point for media coverage and has seen political leadership actively involved in addressing the crisis. Officials from Hubei participated in nationwide teleconferences to coordinate efforts against the outbreak.

Additionally, the residents of Hubei, particularly those from Wuhan, have faced stigma and prejudice as they navigate the repercussions of the outbreak. The province is also involved in patient transfers to ensure better treatment for those affected. Overall, Hubei remains a region significantly impacted by the coronavirus outbreak, but it is actively managing the response and recovery efforts.</data>
      <data key="d2">06e079c3e9edc095ce2abf1424d0adbc,0bc629e093e4342af5865fab7f58e2ed,0f6f81b9c147f34def6ae3e90cdc4a8d,107bf32484dae7a0e0c2c27dae44a96a,13dcf66c4d2749898f0243f4429b9478,1de8f51cd0e0d108a83dabdcd866f67d,203baa1288c7f64829148f9e461d93b8,24930dd33f36a0ab439b76b9f78b2dd2,24f82cd50519ba6e59f128ccf5c821f6,26fd52ba788ccd2a6e5404977738bfda,2c5e9cdd8d1ed971c72785d384814175,3b5ca06477ea6649725a16d09d87927a,5723f9f649f81825f888c51d24c2d1a5,5a58a4c5bcc46fb9d4065918796e6b69,5de6fb969d67797c0c7839a2a6fcf7c5,70a8fc915dd17756704d7e08d2139eaa,81ac5d9d3486351095e7556baea13868,82a05824c63b582fce46f3e7719ac6b6,88c0aa6bc6e9484db48221e353dd96ab,9d9621a0d3abed625eaaf2428ed7b0bb,e74e88082258029f6da479b11ff1f412</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;GUANGZHOU&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
      <data key="d1">Guangzhou is a city in China that has been highlighted as a potential destination for individuals seeking to escape a lockdown situation. Additionally, it is noted that the narrator's family had intended to meet in Guangzhou; however, their travel plans were disrupted due to the outbreak. This indicates that Guangzhou is not only a significant location for travel and family gatherings but also a place affected by the broader challenges posed by the pandemic.</data>
      <data key="d2">2c5e9cdd8d1ed971c72785d384814175,ad43e1b0afe90e62a3b11cf82cc601cf</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;WUHAN INSTITUTE OF VIROLOGY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Wuhan Institute of Virology is a research institute in Wuhan that focuses on virology and has been a subject of global attention during the viral outbreak."</data>
