    </node>
    <node id="&quot;OLD FOX&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Old Fox" is a member of the class of 1977 who is known for hiking the entire Appalachian Trail and documenting his journey. Additionally, "Old Fox" is a nickname for a classmate of the author, who has a familial connection to Mr. Hu Guorui, a former poetry teacher. This multifaceted individual is recognized both for his adventurous spirit and his ties to the literary community through his family connections.</data>
      <data key="d2">477b841f2c30a02cbf570056bfcf7a3d,b311864054a222e4315c575af55fca03</data>
    </node>
