    </node>
    <node id="&quot;MISS LIANG&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">Miss Liang is a nurse from Guangxi who tragically passed away while helping patients in Wuhan during the outbreak. Her death symbolizes the sacrifices made by healthcare workers in the face of the crisis. Reports indicate that she was declared brain dead, further highlighting the tragic loss of life among those dedicated to caring for others during this challenging time.</data>
      <data key="d2">1a74ad918264f9c92231f7eea81aa970,8124652946d2a60444c90e0a3706521b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;ULTRA-LEFTISTS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Ultra-Leftists are described as a group that attacks the author, revealing their perceived shortcomings and influencing public discourse."</data>
      <data key="d2">8127e2d84213dc7f69446ae542408f8b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;CAIXIN&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Caixin is recognized as a platform that has helped the author publish essays, providing crucial support during difficult times."</data>
      <data key="d2">8127e2d84213dc7f69446ae542408f8b</data>
    </node>
    <node id="&quot;HEADLINES TODAY&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Headlines Today is another platform that has assisted the author in publishing their work, contributing to their voice being heard."</data>
      <data key="d2">8127e2d84213dc7f69446ae542408f8b</data>
    </node>
    <edge source="&quot;WUHAN&quot;" target="&quot;WEIBO&quot;">
      <data key="d3">2.0</data>
      <data key="d4">Weibo serves as a vital platform for residents of Wuhan, allowing them to communicate and share their experiences, particularly during challenging times such as the quarantine. For a citizen of Wuhan, Weibo is an essential tool for expressing thoughts and connecting with others. However, the limitations of Weibo have significantly impacted Wuhan's residents, especially during the quarantine period when effective communication is crucial for sharing information and support.</data>
      <data key="d5">2c5e9cdd8d1ed971c72785d384814175,8124652946d2a60444c90e0a3706521b</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;WUHAN&quot;" target="&quot;CHENG YONGXIN&quot;">
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Cheng Yongxin is directly involved in the literary response to the situation in Wuhan, suggesting a way to document the experiences of its residents."</data>
      <data key="d5">2c5e9cdd8d1ed971c72785d384814175</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;WUHAN&quot;" target="&quot;WUHAN DIARY&quot;">
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The concept of Wuhan Diary is directly related to the experiences of those living in Wuhan during the quarantine, aiming to document their stories."</data>
      <data key="d5">2c5e9cdd8d1ed971c72785d384814175</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;WUHAN&quot;" target="&quot;LUNAR NEW YEAR&quot;">
      <data key="d3">8.0</data>
      <data key="d4">The entity "WUHAN" is significantly intertwined with the "LUNAR NEW YEAR" celebrations, particularly during the ongoing health crisis caused by the coronavirus outbreak. The Lunar New Year, a time traditionally associated with family gatherings and cultural festivities, has been profoundly affected by the quarantine measures implemented in Wuhan. This situation highlights the stark contrast between the usual celebratory atmosphere and the current crisis, as community gatherings and travel have been severely restricted.

During this period, approximately five million people evacuated from Wuhan, further impacting the city's population dynamics amidst the outbreak. The celebrations, which typically bring joy and togetherness, have been disrupted, leading to a pervasive sense of loss and grief among the residents. The timing of the niece's evacuation flight was also linked to the Lunar New Year, underscoring the personal and communal challenges faced during this festive season.

Overall, the events in Wuhan during the Lunar New Year illustrate the cultural significance of the holiday while simultaneously revealing the profound disruptions caused by the health crisis, affecting both the community's ability to celebrate and the emotional well-being of its residents.</data>
      <data key="d5">0bc629e093e4342af5865fab7f58e2ed,2c5e9cdd8d1ed971c72785d384814175,3f8704dd72f25d452df3dea8b46c7b79,941fd97efac4d3db43e927529ff925c4,96d1b9c58350b57745013c6971a006ff,a47098bdb1e8c07bb54ff29a75698044,c74fab649e0e555219cd986800fcd418,e8105e46cc3831c70abcbabad8edbcaf</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;WUHAN&quot;" target="&quot;HUBEI&quot;">
      <data key="d3">16.0</data>
      <data key="d4">Wuhan is a major city and the capital of Hubei province, which has been significantly impacted by the coronavirus outbreak. The outbreak has led to heightened infection rates in Wuhan, prompting stringent quarantine measures that are particularly focused on this city. As a result, both Wuhan and Hubei province have experienced various challenges, including regional stigma and conflict as workers return to the area. The health crisis has not only affected the city but also reflects broader issues within the province, highlighting the interconnectedness of their healthcare situations. The governance and outbreak response are being managed at the provincial level, with Wuhan serving as a key location in the overall response to the viral outbreak.</data>
      <data key="d5">06e079c3e9edc095ce2abf1424d0adbc,0bc629e093e4342af5865fab7f58e2ed,0f6f81b9c147f34def6ae3e90cdc4a8d,107bf32484dae7a0e0c2c27dae44a96a,13dcf66c4d2749898f0243f4429b9478,1de8f51cd0e0d108a83dabdcd866f67d,203baa1288c7f64829148f9e461d93b8,24930dd33f36a0ab439b76b9f78b2dd2,26fd52ba788ccd2a6e5404977738bfda,2c5e9cdd8d1ed971c72785d384814175,5a58a4c5bcc46fb9d4065918796e6b69,5de6fb969d67797c0c7839a2a6fcf7c5,70a8fc915dd17756704d7e08d2139eaa,82a05824c63b582fce46f3e7719ac6b6,9d9621a0d3abed625eaaf2428ed7b0bb,e74e88082258029f6da479b11ff1f412</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;WUHAN&quot;" target="&quot;GUANGZHOU&quot;">
      <data key="d3">2.0</data>
      <data key="d4">Wuhan and Guangzhou are interconnected cities that have been significantly impacted by the recent outbreak. The lockdown imposed in Wuhan has directly affected travel plans to Guangzhou, illustrating the close relationship between the two locations during this quarantine period. This situation highlights how the measures taken in one city can influence the dynamics and travel arrangements in another, emphasizing the broader implications of the outbreak on urban connectivity.</data>
      <data key="d5">2c5e9cdd8d1ed971c72785d384814175,ad43e1b0afe90e62a3b11cf82cc601cf</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;WUHAN&quot;" target="&quot;SINGAPORE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">2.0</data>
      <data key="d4">Wuhan and Singapore are interconnected through a situation of concern and assistance during an outbreak. Singapore is actively making arrangements for its citizens to return from Wuhan, demonstrating a commitment to the safety and well-being of its nationals. Additionally, Singapore serves as the destination for the evacuation of a niece, further emphasizing the efforts being made to facilitate safe returns from Wuhan amid the ongoing circumstances.</data>
      <data key="d5">a47098bdb1e8c07bb54ff29a75698044,ad43e1b0afe90e62a3b11cf82cc601cf</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;WUHAN&quot;" target="&quot;THE GOVERNMENT OFFICIALS&quot;">
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Government Officials are responsible for managing the situation in Wuhan, which is currently chaotic due to the outbreak."</data>
      <data key="d5">ad43e1b0afe90e62a3b11cf82cc601cf</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;WUHAN&quot;" target="&quot;CHINESE NEW YEAR&quot;">
      <data key="d3">3.0</data>
      <data key="d4">Wuhan is currently facing significant challenges due to the ongoing coronavirus outbreak, which has coincided with the celebration of the Chinese New Year. The holiday is complicating the quarantine situation in the city, highlighting a temporal relationship between the event and the ongoing health crisis. As a result, the festivities associated with the Chinese New Year are overshadowed by the difficulties posed by the outbreak, affecting celebrations and gatherings in Wuhan.</data>
      <data key="d5">4c6ae1a529eeabbb8b203fca0dffe928,9d9621a0d3abed625eaaf2428ed7b0bb,ad43e1b0afe90e62a3b11cf82cc601cf</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;WUHAN&quot;" target="&quot;THE INFECTED COUPLE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Infected Couple resides in Wuhan, linking their health status directly to the city's current outbreak situation."</data>
      <data key="d5">ad43e1b0afe90e62a3b11cf82cc601cf</data>
    </edge>
