    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;WUHAN&quot;" target="&quot;DIRECTOR JIANG XUEQING&quot;">
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Director Jiang Xueqing worked at Wuhan Central Hospital, contributing to the healthcare system in Wuhan during the coronavirus outbreak."</data>
      <data key="d5">2d702d808dc0983b5a009535ca71a6c6</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;WUHAN&quot;" target="&quot;LI WENLIANG&quot;">
      <data key="d3">5.0</data>
      <data key="d4">Li Wenliang is a prominent figure associated with the city of Wuhan, where he served as a doctor during the early stages of the coronavirus outbreak. He is widely recognized for his courageous efforts to raise awareness about the virus, highlighting the challenges faced by the city and its residents during the epidemic. His warnings about the coronavirus not only underscored the severity of the situation in Wuhan but also resonated deeply with the local population, symbolizing their struggles and resilience in the face of adversity. The impact of Li Wenliang's passing is profound, marking a moment of loss and reflection for many in Wuhan, as his story continues to embody the collective experience of the community during this critical time. Through his actions, Li Wenliang played a crucial role in addressing the outbreak, making his contributions directly relevant to the city's ongoing battle against the virus.</data>
      <data key="d5">2d702d808dc0983b5a009535ca71a6c6,603d63bc59fd873441e2c2b5e86f64e6,8475b5acce1676914c613935d50901d6,a13ce419c16c812171a8f0609ebcfb47,f7d4aedaaebf83b5bb28320eecdc7d6c</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;WUHAN&quot;" target="&quot;LI YUEHUA&quot;">
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Li Yuehua's treatment methods are being discussed in the context of the urgent health crisis faced by the people in Wuhan."</data>
      <data key="d5">68d1018c902661392b4e20435e4961ad</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;WUHAN&quot;" target="&quot;CHANG KAI&quot;">
      <data key="d3">2.0</data>
      <data key="d4">Chang Kai is a victim of the coronavirus outbreak in Wuhan, symbolizing the profound human cost of the crisis that has impacted the city. His final words are intricately linked to the narrative surrounding the Wuhan community's response to the outbreak and their ongoing pursuit of justice. Through his story, Chang Kai embodies the struggles and resilience of those affected by the pandemic in Wuhan.</data>
      <data key="d5">8124652946d2a60444c90e0a3706521b,c8e229d8fbd4f477126682d1b67e1bfd</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;WUHAN&quot;" target="&quot;INVESTIGATIVE REPORTS&quot;">
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Investigative reports are essential for documenting the experiences of Wuhan residents during the coronavirus outbreak, ensuring that the events are not forgotten."</data>
      <data key="d5">c8e229d8fbd4f477126682d1b67e1bfd</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;WUHAN&quot;" target="&quot;THE HOSPITAL ADMINISTRATOR&quot;">
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
