    <edge source="&quot;HUBEI WRITERS ASSOCIATION&quot;" target="&quot;CHINESE COMMUNIST PARTY&quot;">
      <data key="d3">2.0</data>
      <data key="d4">The Hubei Writers Association and the Chinese Communist Party have a collaborative relationship that serves multiple purposes. The Chinese Communist Party works alongside organizations such as the Hubei Writers Association to offer community support, particularly during challenging times like outbreaks. Additionally, the Hubei Writers Association engages with the Chinese Communist Party in discussions concerning regulations that impact writers, indicating a proactive involvement in shaping the literary landscape within the region. This interaction highlights the association's role in both community support and regulatory dialogue, reflecting a partnership that benefits both entities.</data>
      <data key="d5">203baa1288c7f64829148f9e461d93b8,973c13961f84e95436b515301155082a</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;HUBEI WRITERS ASSOCIATION&quot;" target="&quot;CHANGJIANG LITERATURE AND ART MAGAZINE&quot;">
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"The Hubei Writers Association supports writers like those contributing to the Changjiang Literature and Art Magazine, indicating a connection in cultural efforts during recovery."</data>
      <data key="d5">fd7d025a46189bb316ef893020b7e22d</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;HUBEI WRITERS ASSOCIATION&quot;" target="&quot;FANG FANG&quot;">
      <data key="d3">2.0</data>
      <data key="d4">Fang Fang served as the chair of the Hubei Writers Association, where she played a significant role in engaging with government officials on regulations and issues that impacted writers. Through her leadership, she influenced the literary community in Hubei, contributing to the development and advocacy of writers' interests in the region.</data>
      <data key="d5">4a02f8de11375d220370828d6659eaf3,973c13961f84e95436b515301155082a</data>
    </edge>
