    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LI WENLIANG&quot;" target="&quot;HUBEI GOVERNMENT&quot;">
      <data key="d3">2.0</data>
      <data key="d4">Li Wenliang was a whistleblower who raised alarms about the outbreak of a novel coronavirus in Wuhan, Hubei Province. The Hubei Government faced significant criticism for its handling of the outbreak, particularly concerning the treatment of Li Wenliang and his early warnings about the virus. In response to the backlash, the Hubei Government has been involved in both the investigation of the circumstances surrounding Li Wenliang's actions and the commemoration of his contributions during the outbreak.</data>
      <data key="d5">603d63bc59fd873441e2c2b5e86f64e6,e61ec0b2352248237abc9e924d1f0062</data>
    </edge>
    <edge source="&quot;LI WENLIANG&quot;" target="&quot;ZENG GUANG&quot;">
      <data key="d3">1.0</data>
      <data key="d4">"Zeng Guang's comments highlight the lack of awareness about Li Wenliang's contributions during the outbreak response."</data>
      <data key="d5">2014d81b9f4aeb008dab606a9f719b7a</data>
    </edge>
